%N A055440 Distribution of first digit of mantissa following Benford's law, using d'Hondt method.
%C A055440 This is the subsequence of terms less than 10 in A395154.
%H A055440 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A055440/b055440.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A055440 J. Connelly, <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20030803204148/http://www.solent.ac.uk/socsci/jc/voting/glossary.html">Glossary of voting terms</a>.
%H A055440 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/BenfordsLaw.html">Benford's Law</a>.
%H A055440 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%27Hondt_method">D'Hondt method</a>.
%H A055440 <a href="/index/Be#Benford">Index entries for sequences related to Benford's law</a>.
%F A055440 Positions of k are given by n_k(m) = Sum_{j=1..9} floor(m*log(1+1/j)/log(1+1/k)), m >= 1. - _Pontus von Brömssen_, Apr 21 2026
%e A055440 a(50)=1 so that after 50 terms we have had 16 1's, 9 2's, 6 3's, 5 4's, 4 5's, 3 6's, 3 7's, 2 8's and 2 9's
%Y A055440 Cf. A055439, A055441, A055442, A395154.
%K A055440 nonn,base,changed
%O A055440 1,2
%A A055440 _Henry Bottomley_, May 17 2000
